main event: A witness reported seeing an unidentified flying object in Aberdean, South Dakota, on April 8, 1965.
interesting points: The witness was accompanied by their wife, who also saw the object,The object was in sight for approximately 2 hours and 5 seconds,The object reportedly changed position and went back up after being observed,The witness had a professional background in insurance, contributing credibility to the report,The report was sent to the Air Police Base at Minot, N.D., but was initially dismissed.
witness description: A 23-year-old male with a B.A. degree, working in an insurance company.
